117→
118→Project: ${projectName}
119→${sessionSummary ? `Session Summary: ${sessionSummary}\n` : ''}
120→--- CONVERSATION ---
121→${formattedMessages}
122→--- END CONVERSATION ---
123→
124→Extract insights in this JSON format:
125→{
126→  "summary": {
127→    "title": "Brief title describing main accomplishment (max 60 chars)",
128→    "content": "2-3 sentence narrative of what was accomplished",
129→    "bullets": ["Key point 1", "Key point 2", "Key point 3"]
130→  },
131→  "decisions": [
132→    {
133→      "title": "The specific decision made (max 60 chars)",
134→      "content": "Detailed explanation with concrete details",
135→      "reasoning": "Why this choice was made over alternatives",
136→      "alternatives": ["Alternative 1 considered", "Alternative 2 considered"],
137→      "confidence": 85,
138→      "evidence": ["User#4: ...", "Assistant#5: ..."]
139→    }
140→  ],
141→  "learnings": [
142→    {
143→      "title": "Specific thing learned (max 60 chars)",
144→      "content": "Detailed explanation with concrete details",
145→      "context": "When/where this applies and why it matters",
146→      "confidence": 80,
147→      "evidence": ["User#7: ...", "Assistant#8: ..."]
148→    }
149→  ]
150→}
151→
152→Only include insights rated 70+ confidence. If you cannot cite evidence, drop the insight. Return empty arrays for categories with no strong insights. Max 3 decisions, 5 learnings.
153→Evidence should reference the labeled turns in the conversation (e.g., "User#2", "Assistant#5").
154→
155→Respond with valid JSON only, wrapped in <json>...</json> tags. Do not include any other text.`;
